sql:
SELECT status_name 
FROM service_status 
WHERE status_id = 1;

SELECT shelter_type
FROM shelter_types
WHERE capacity > 3;

external_knowledge:
External knowledge:
- "inactive" refers to bus stops that are currently not in service;
- "low ridership" refers to a predefined threshold of average ridership, e.g., below 100 passengers per day;
- "maintenance due" refers to bus stops that have a scheduled maintenance date in the past.
